[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/takeout_doubles"]
[Student "S"]
{The bidding has been as shown.   

Now that West has stolen your response you aren't strong enough to make a free-bid at the 2-level. You pass, East bids 2\D and partner doubles again. Now what? 

This is not a penalty double, partner is merely repeating his request for you to name a suit. But now he expects you to choose between \Hs and \Cs.

You bid 3\C and everybody passes.

You may be one too high, but that still might be a good score if they can make 2\D.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "S:6.87.AKQJ63.J963 A975.KJ3.97.KQ52 KQJT42.A42.T5.T7 83.QT965.842.A84"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "2H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1D X 1S 2H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "cbd53dff9b3a8144834709fca28e011c2d95d4026a36769932efd64233737764"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/takeout_doubles"]
[Student "S"]
{The bidding has been as shown.   

After North bids you are no longer forced to respond to partner's Takeout Double. You may pass is you want to.

But if you don't pass you are making what is called a "free bid". You should have 6 or more points and a reason for wanting to bid - like your 5-card \H suit.

You bid 2\H and everybody passes.}

